quran[37]{c,v,t}:
  19,22,So she was pregnant (with) him so she distantly isolated herself with him (to) a far/remote place/position
  19,23,"So the labour/childbirth came to her to (at) the palm tree`s trunk/stem, she said: \"Oh I wish I would have died before this and I was forgotten (and long) forgotten"
  19,24,"So he (Jesus) called her from below/beneath her: \"That do not be sad/grieving, your Lord had put below/beneath you a stream/clearance of a burden/generosity"
  19,25,"And shake/move to(wards) you with the palm tree`s trunk/stem, it causes freshly harvested/gathered ripe/moist (dates) to fall/drop repeatedly on you"
  19,26,"So eat and drink and be delighted/satisfied eye(s) (delight your eyes), so when you see anyone from the human, so say: `That I made a duty/vow (on myself) to the merciful, a fast , so I will not converse/speak the day/today (to) a human"
  19,27,"So she came with him (to) her nation carrying him , they said: \"You Mary, you had come (with) a strange and confusing thing"
  19,28,"You Aaron`s sister, your father was not (a) human/man of bad/evil , and your mother was not an fornicatress/adulteress/prostitute"
  19,29,"So she pointed/indicated to him, they said: \"How (do) we converse/speak (to) whom was in the crib/cradle a boy/child/infant"
  19,30,"He said: \"That I am God`s worshipper/slave, He gave/brought me The Book and He made me a prophet"
  19,31,"And He made me blessed, wherever I was/am, and He directed/commanded me with the prayers and the charity/purification as long as I continued/lasted alive"
  19,32,"And charitable/obedient with my mother, and He did not make me a miserable/unhappy tyrant/rebel"
  19,33,"And the security/peace (was) on me (on the) day I was born, and (the) day I die, and (the) day I be sent/resurrected/revived alive"
  19,34,"That (was) Jesus Mary`s son, the correct/real saying/opinion and belief which they (are) doubting/arguing in it"
  19,35,"(It) was not to God that (He) take from a child/children (son), His praise/glory, if He ordered/executed amatter/command , so but He says to it: \"Be, so it becomes"
  19,36,"And that God (is) my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him, that (is) a straight/direct road/way"
  19,37,"So the groups/parties differed/disagreed/disputed from between them, so grief/distress to those who disbelieved from an assembly of a great day"
  19,38,"Make (to) hear/listen with them, and make to see/understand , a day they come to Us, but the unjust/oppressive today (are) in evident misguidance"
  19,39,"And warn/give them notice (of) the Grief`s Day/Resurrection Day, when the matter/affair was accomplished/carried out , and they are in negligence/disregard, and they are not believing"
  19,40,"That We, We inhabit the earth/Planet Earth, and who (is) on it, and to Us they return"
  19,41,"And remember/mention in The Book Abraham, that he truly was an always very truthful prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father: \"You my father, for what (do) you worship what does not hear/listen, and nor see/understand , and nor enrich/suffice from you a thing"
  19,43,"You my father, that I, (it) had come to me from the knowledge, what did not come to you, so follow me, I guide you a straight/level road/way"
  19,44,"You my father, do not worship the devil, that the devil was/is to the merciful disobedient"
  19,45,"You my father, that I fear that torture touches you from the merciful, so you be to the devil an ally/follower"
  19,46,"He said: \"Are you shunning/turning away from my gods, you Abraham? If (E) you do not end/terminate/stop, I will stone you, and leave/distance me a long/life time"
  19,47,"He said: \"Security/peace on you, I will ask for forgiveness for you (from) my Lord, that He truly (was) with me generous/blessing"
  19,48,"And I separate/isolate myself from you and what you call from other than God, and I call my Lord, maybe/perhaps that I not be with my Lord`s call/prayer miserable/unhappy"
  19,49,"So when he separated/isolated himself from them, and what they call from other than God, We granted for him Issac , and Jacob and each/all, We made a prophet"
  19,50,"And We granted for them from Our mercy, and We made for them (a) truthful high and mighty/dignified tongue/language/speech"
  19,51,"And remember/mention in The Book Moses, that he truly was faithful/loyal/devoted and (he) was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,52,"And We called him from the mountain`s side/direction, the right (side), and We neared/approached him secretly conversing"
  19,53,"And We granted for him from Our mercy his brother Aaron, a prophet"
  19,54,"And remember/mention in The Book Ishmael , that he truly was truthful (in) the promise, and was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,55,"And (he) was ordering/commanding his family/people with the prayers and the charity/purification, and (he) was at his Lord accepted/approved"
  19,56,"And remember/mention in The Book Idris, that he truly was always very truthful, and a prophet"
  19,57,And We raised him a high and mighty/dignified place/position
  19,58,"Those are those who God blessed/praised on them from the prophets from Adam`s descendants; and from who We carried with Noah, , and from Abraham`s and Ishmael`s descendants, and from who We guided and We chose/purified, if the merciful`s verses/evidences are read/recited on them they fell down prostrating and weeping"